tsm-app (1.1.6-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Add: Anniversary and Classic Era realms now appear in the Add Realm
    dropdown; fetched from extraAnniversaryRealms/extraClassicRealms in the
    status endpoint and merged with the realms2/list response.
  * Add: character filter relaxed for Anniversary/Classic Era - falls through
    when no active characters are found so manually-added realms still appear.
  * Fix: replace python3-pyside6 with individual Qt module packages
    (python3-pyside6.qtcore/qtgui/qtnetwork/qtsvg/qtwidgets) - the monolithic
    package does not exist on Ubuntu 26.04; PySide6 is absent from apt on
    Ubuntu 24.04 and earlier entirely (use pip/wheel on those versions).
  * Fix: bundle APScheduler 4.x, structlog, and tomli-w inside the package at
    /usr/lib/tsm-app/ - Ubuntu repos only carry APScheduler 3.x which is
    incompatible with this app; shell wrapper sets PYTHONPATH automatically.
  * Fix: entry script now uses python3 shebang and version-agnostic install
    path; the previous pip-generated wrapper used /usr/bin/python (absent on
    Ubuntu 26.04) and a Python-version-pinned dist-packages directory.

