tsm-app (1.1.3-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Change: WoW path storage unified to base directory; game-version paths derived
    on demand. Old configs with _retail_ paths migrated automatically on load.
  * Change: Settings dialog now saves manually typed WoW path on Done.
  * Change: Settings Browse saves single base path instead of per-version entries.
  * Change: AddonWriterService writes AppData.lua to all installed game versions.
  * Change: path utilities consolidated in tsm/wow/utils.py.
  * Fix: startup race condition where scan() could overwrite config-loaded WoW
    install paths with an empty list, causing a persistent AppHelper-not-found
    warning even when the install is correctly configured. Closes #3.
  * UI: Settings WoW Directory field now shows a hint label (base folder containing
    _retail_, _classic_, etc.) with a path example.
  * UI: Settings Browse dialog now opens at the currently entered directory.
  * UI: Login dialog tightened (480x240); subtitle label removed; placeholder
    changed to "Email".
  * UI: Login HTTP errors mapped to concise messages (401 -> invalid credentials,
    etc.) instead of exposing raw exception text.
  * Feature: Log viewer window accessible via new status bar button. Shows
    session log records in a styled table with level color-coding and row
    wrapping. Copy to Clipboard redacts email addresses before copying.

